---
import IndicatorLayout from '../../layouts/IndicatorLayout.astro';

const indicatorId = 'aroonosc';
const indicatorName = 'Aroon Oscillator';
const description = `The Aroon Oscillator is a trend-following indicator that combines the Aroon Up and Aroon Down lines into a single oscillator. It measures the difference between these two components, oscillating between -100 and +100, providing a clear view of trend strength and direction in one line.`;
const parameters = [
  {
    "name": "period",
    "type": "number",
    "default": 25,
    "min": 10,
    "max": 100,
    "description": "Number of periods to look back for highs and lows"
  }
];
---

<IndicatorLayout
  indicatorId={indicatorId}
  indicatorName={indicatorName}
  description={description}
  parameters={parameters}
>
  <h2>Overview</h2>
  <p>
    The Aroon Oscillator is a single-line indicator derived from the Aroon Indicator system created by Tushar Chande. 
    It simplifies the dual-line Aroon system by calculating the difference between Aroon Up and Aroon Down, resulting 
    in an oscillator that swings between -100 and +100. This consolidation makes it easier to quickly assess market 
    conditions and trend strength.
  </p>
  <p>
    The oscillator provides a clear, unambiguous signal about the dominant force in the market. Positive values indicate 
    bullish pressure (recent highs are more recent than lows), while negative values indicate bearish pressure. The 
    magnitude of the oscillator value indicates the strength of the trend.
  </p>

  <h2>How It Works</h2>
  <p>The Aroon Oscillator is calculated in two steps:</p>
  <ol>
    <li><strong>Calculate Aroon Up and Down:</strong> Same as the standard Aroon Indicator</li>
    <li><strong>Calculate the Oscillator:</strong> Subtract Aroon Down from Aroon Up</li>
  </ol>
  
  <div class="not-prose bg-gray-100 dark:bg-gray-800 p-4 rounded-lg my-4 border border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700">
    <p class="font-mono text-sm mb-0 text-gray-800 dark:text-gray-200"> Aroon Up = ((Period - Periods Since Highest High) / Period) × 100<br/>
      Aroon Down = ((Period - Periods Since Lowest Low) / Period) × 100<br/>
      <br/>
      Aroon Oscillator = Aroon Up - Aroon Down<br/>
      <br/>
      Range: -100 to +100
    </p>
  </div>

  <h2>Key Features</h2>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Single Line:</strong> Simplifies the two-line Aroon system into one oscillator</li>
    <li><strong>Centered Oscillator:</strong> Zero line clearly separates bullish from bearish conditions</li>
    <li><strong>Bounded Range:</strong> Always between -100 and +100 for easy interpretation</li>
    <li><strong>Trend Strength:</strong> Distance from zero indicates trend strength</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Interpretation & Trading Signals</h2>
  
  <h3>Value Ranges</h3>
  <div class="not-prose bg-blue-50 dark:bg-blue-950/30 p-4 rounded-lg my-4 border border-blue-200 dark:border-blue-800">
    <h4 class="font-semibold mb-2 text-lg text-blue-900 dark:text-blue-100"> Oscillator Values:</h4> <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-4 text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300"> <li><strong class="text-gray-900 dark:text-gray-100"> +50 to +100:</strong> Strong uptrend</li>
      <li><strong class="text-gray-900 dark:text-gray-100">0 to +50:</strong> Weak uptrend or consolidation</li>
      <li><strong class="text-gray-900 dark:text-gray-100">0 to -50:</strong> Weak downtrend or consolidation</li>
      <li><strong class="text-gray-900 dark:text-gray-100">-50 to -100:</strong> Strong downtrend</li>
    </ul>
    
    <h4 class="font-semibold mb-2 text-lg text-blue-900 dark:text-blue-100"> Key Signals:</h4> <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300"> <li><strong class="text-gray-900 dark:text-gray-100"> Cross above zero:</strong> Bullish signal (uptrend beginning)</li>
      <li><strong class="text-gray-900 dark:text-gray-100"> Cross below zero:</strong> Bearish signal (downtrend beginning)</li>
      <li><strong class="text-gray-900 dark:text-gray-100"> At +100:</strong> Maximum bullish strength (new high just occurred)</li>
      <li><strong class="text-gray-900 dark:text-gray-100"> At -100:</strong> Maximum bearish strength (new low just occurred)</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <h3>Trading Strategies</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Zero Line Crossovers:</strong>
      <ul>
        <li>Buy when oscillator crosses above zero</li>
        <li>Sell when oscillator crosses below zero</li>
      </ul>
    </li>
    <li><strong>Threshold Signals:</strong>
      <ul>
        <li>Strong buy: Oscillator rises above +50</li>
        <li>Strong sell: Oscillator falls below -50</li>
      </ul>
    </li>
    <li><strong>Divergence Trading:</strong>
      <ul>
        <li>Bullish divergence: Price makes lower lows while oscillator makes higher lows</li>
        <li>Bearish divergence: Price makes higher highs while oscillator makes lower highs</li>
      </ul>
    </li>
    <li><strong>Trend Confirmation:</strong> Use extreme readings (above +70 or below -70) to confirm strong trends</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Advanced Interpretation</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Oscillator Slope:</strong> Rising oscillator indicates strengthening bullish momentum</li>
    <li><strong>Time at Extremes:</strong> Extended periods above +50 or below -50 indicate persistent trends</li>
    <li><strong>Quick Reversals:</strong> Rapid moves from -100 to +100 (or vice versa) signal sharp trend changes</li>
    <li><strong>Consolidation Zones:</strong> Oscillator between -25 and +25 often indicates ranging market</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Practical Application</h2>
  
  <h3>Strengths</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>Simplifies trend analysis into a single line</li>
    <li>Clear bullish/bearish demarcation at zero</li>
    <li>Easy to spot trend changes and strength</li>
    <li>Works well across different timeframes</li>
    <li>No complex calculations or multiple lines to track</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Limitations</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>Still a lagging indicator based on historical highs/lows</li>
    <li>Can oscillate frequently in choppy markets</li>
    <li>Less detail than the full two-line Aroon system</li>
    <li>May miss subtle changes visible in separate lines</li>
    <li>Requires additional confirmation in ranging markets</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Combination with Other Indicators</h2>
  <p>The Aroon Oscillator pairs well with:</p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>ADX:</strong> Aroon for direction, ADX for trend strength validation</li>
    <li><strong>RSI:</strong> Combine trend direction with momentum extremes</li>
    <li><strong>Moving Averages:</strong> Use Aroon Oscillator to time MA crossover trades</li>
    <li><strong>MACD:</strong> Compare momentum signals for confirmation</li>
    <li><strong>Volume Indicators:</strong> Ensure trend changes are supported by volume</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Example Usage</h2>
  <p>Code examples will be available once the Rust implementation is complete.</p>
  </div>

  <h2>Mathematical Background</h2>
  <p>
    The Aroon Oscillator elegantly combines two time-based measurements into a single value. By subtracting Aroon Down 
    from Aroon Up, it creates a normalized measure of which extreme (high or low) occurred more recently. The oscillator's 
    bounded range (-100 to +100) makes it easy to compare across different securities and timeframes.
  </p>
  <p>
    The mathematical simplicity of the oscillator (a simple subtraction) belies its effectiveness. It captures the essence 
    of the Aroon system—measuring the recency of extremes—while providing clearer signals through the zero line crossover 
    mechanism. This makes it particularly useful for systematic trading strategies and scanning multiple securities.
  </p>

</IndicatorLayout>
